@sdcheeran: You've asked "does loading the new one help or hurt overall transfer speeds".

It depends on your upload/download capabilities. Only guys with rely fast connections can afford that. I can't. You cannot too. My general advice always have been to avoid loading of two torrents which are in initial-seeding phase (simultaneously). 2nd, if someone needs/must join to initial swarm AND have borderline speed capabilities (UL speed 35-50 kB/s) best and probably only way for avoid flagging as "leeching scumbag" is to STOP ANY OTHER torrent and left active only specific one, with speed settings on UNLIMITED (both UL and DL).

